You can use `cy.$$(&#39;selector&#39;)` to *synchronously* query for an element (jquery).

If you want this to happen after a cypress command, you&#39;ll need a `.then`:

```js
cy.visit(&#39;/&#39;)
cy.get(&#39;element-one&#39;).then(() =&gt; {
  const $el2 = cy.$$(&#39;element-two&#39;)
  if ($el2.length) {
    // do this
  } else {
    // do that
  }
})
```

